Africa’s richest man and Nigeria’s business mogul, Alhaji Aliko Dangote has hinted on his intention to hire an expatriate to man the N3 billion skills acquisition centre built by the Kano state government and named after him. Dangote, who accompanied the state governor, Dr Abdullahi Ganduje  on a tour of the site commended the administration for the laudable project which he said will arrest the unemployment challenges in the state and the country at large. He said the billion naira centre is the first of its kind in Nigeria and promised to employ the best manager  with remarkable experience for the place. The  business mogul said the centre will be run by competent hands that will transform it  into world class centre that will attract the west African sub region. Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje said the skill centre, which is strategically situated outside the metropolis, will train young men and women in more than 24 various skills and prepare them for future endeavors in line with global best practices. He said the centre is one of his government resolve to tackle unemployment amongst youth and that a date will soon be announced for its commissioning.